data.description: STUNNING ACRCHITECTURAL DETAILS AND CHARMING CURB APPEAL WITH A HINT OF HISTORICAL FLARE. YOU WILL BE AMAZED WITH THE TWO STORY HIGH FRONT PORCH WITH STATELY COLUMNS  AND ORNATE FRONT ENTRY WITH WALL SCOUNCE LIGHTING. The house has had many updates and has been well maintained. In recent years the house has been painted, AC System, Hot Water Heater, Gas Logs, Roof, 200 Amp Service. And be sure to check out the recently installed concrete patio with reclaimed brick paver edging and bordering. The current owners had this amazing patio installed so they could enjoy the wonderful private back yard for many years to come not anticipating having to leave it so soon. If you work remotely this four bedroom two bath house can easily be used as a three bedroom with a home office or bonus room depending on your personal needs. Currently the primary bedroom on the main level is being used as a bonus room space. The vaulted great room has gorgeous exposed wood beams with a stone façade fireplace with custom built ins on both sides. The fireplace has a remote controlled Texas Bonfire gas log set that has been installed recently. The kitchen is open to the vaulted great room and there is a wall of windows and an access door that leads out to the patio. You will love the outdoor living space. If you enjoy entertaining then you will appreciate the functionality of this wonderful house. The kitchen has an abundance of cabinet space and a large center island for prep space, hosting guests or working on homework. This spectacular house is located just minutes from Downtown Greenville, SC which has been recognized as one of the top ten cities in America.
